reviews.text: Cute little local railway station with regular, but not very frequent, service to Bedford and Bletchley

Incredibly basic and standard with the only recent addition being the installation of a new ticket machine on one side of the station which is nice. Facilities and services are bare however both platforms have step free access.

This railway is disabled/wheelchair bound person friendly. Both platforms have ramps not stairs. There are no installed CCTV cameras on any of the platforms. There is a emergency help button to communicate with staff. This station is unmanned. The only CCTV I could see was installed on the pub building. This station is not security friendly. Not my ideal station for night travel.
Pretty station on a pretty railway line in a pretty village / town served by cool, old diesel trains that proper chug along.
Amazing town with villagey feel, very close to Woburn. Sublime.
